<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>JS Executer</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            background-color: #f4f4f4;
        }
        .container {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 50px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        h1, h2 {
            text-align: center;
        }
        label {
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        form{
            margin: 20px;
            margin-right: 40px;
        }
        textarea {
            width: 100%;
            padding: 10px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 5px;
            resize: vertical;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #007bff;
            color: #fff;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #0056b3;
        }
        pre {
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            padding: 10px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            overflow-x: auto;
        }
        .intro {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            background-color: #f9f9f9;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Welcome to JS Executer</h1>
        <div class="intro">
            <p>This is a beta version of JS Executer. The idea behind it is to give students the ability to execute JavaScript easily with one click and in a safe environment. The JavaScript code does not pass through any dangerous functions like <code>eval()</code> in our app. In fact, the code is being executed in a completely different application.</p>
            <p>Enjoy!</p>
        </div>
        <h2>Execute JavaScript</h2>
        <form id="jsForm">
            <label for="jsCode">Enter JavaScript code:</label><br>
            <textarea id="jsCode" name="code" rows="10" cols="50"></textarea><br>
            <button type="submit">Execute</button>
        </form>

        <div id="resultContainer" style="display: none;">
            <h2>Execution Result:</h2>
            <pre id="result"></pre>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        document.getElementById('jsForm').addEventListener('submit', async function(event) {
            event.preventDefault();
            
            const formData = new FormData(this);
            const jsCode = formData.get('code');

            const response = await fetch('/beta', {
                method: 'POST',
                headers: {
                    'Content-Type': 'application/json'
                },
                body: JSON.stringify({ code: jsCode })
            });

            const resultData = await response.json();
            const resultContainer = document.getElementById('resultContainer');
            const resultElement = document.getElementById('result');

            resultElement.textContent = JSON.stringify(resultData, null, 4);
            resultContainer.style.display = 'block';
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
